            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EHow%20furious%20Satan%20was%20at%20Job%2C%20a%20man%20who%20was%20%22blameless%2C%20a%20man%20of%20complete%20integrity.%20He%20feared%20God%20and%20stayed%20away%20from%20evil%22%20(Job%201%3A1).%20Satan%20continually%20plotted%2C%20planned%2C%20and%20accused%20Job%20before%20God%20until%20God%20finally%20gave%20him%20permission%20to%20breach%20the%20protective%20hedge%20(vv.%2010-12).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EHow%20could%20God%20do%20such%20a%20thing%3F%20He%20had%20confidence%20that%20Job%20would%20continue%20to%20serve%20Him%2C%20regardless%20of%20circumstances%2C%20and%20that%20Job%20would%20prevail%20over%20the%20enemy.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%22The%20wicked%20plot%20against%20the%20godly%20.%20.%20.%20but%20the%20Lord%20just%20laughs%2C%20for%20he%20sees%20their%20day%20of%20judgment%20coming%22%20(Psalm%2037%3A12-13).%20How%20can%20God%20laugh%20when%20we%20are%20under%20such%20attack%20by%20the%20wicked%3F%20The%20Bible%20records%20that%20God%20laughs%20only%20when%20someone%20threatens%20Him%3A%20%22Let%20us%20break%20their%20chains%2C%22%20they%20cry%2C%20%22and%20free%20ourselves%20from%20this%20slavery.%22%20But%20the%20one%20who%20rules%20in%20heaven%20laughs.%20The%20Lord%20scoffs%20at%20them%22%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E(Psalm%202%3A3-4).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EGod%20has%20no%20problem%20with%20confidence%2C%20and%20He%20also%20has%20confidence%20in%20you%2C%20or%20He%20would%20not%20allow%20you%20to%20encounter%20trials.%20When%20you%20laugh%20at%20the%20enemy's%20attack%2C%20you%20are%20simply%20treating%20Satan%20the%20way%20God%20treats%20him.%20Pass%20on%20through%20your%20trial%20with%20the%20laughter%20of%20God%20in%20your%20mouth.%20He%20is%20not%20threatened%2C%20and%20neither%20should%20you%20be!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
